<br>
I have never heard of a police dog losing it. That's not to say that there hasn't been any that have, but I would imagine it is very, very rare. Most dog attacks can be attributed to poor training or leaving the dog unattended when they shouldn't be (like leaving them alone with children). A well trained dog is an under control dog and poses no danger while supervised imo.<br>
<br>
The one thing I do hate is small children being left alone with dogs. My kids were never left alone with our dogs, even though I trusted 100% the dogs would never harm them. The thing is, until a child hits puberty they do not give off a human scent, so you can never be 100% certain how a dog perceives them.<br>
<br>
I am sure there are those who disagree, but imo, you should never leave a dog alone with a small child, no matter how much you may trust them. <p><br>
