What I'm wondering about is *responsibility*. I understand that these dogs are treated like officers and have the same ramifications if you do something to them, but what about the dog's actions? The dog is not responsible. Humans are responsible, dogs are not. Well, some humans anyway. But who have they deemed &quot;Responsible For What The Dog Does&quot;? If for some reason a police dog decides to tear me a new asshole while im walking down the street, who's ass am I going to send down the river in court? If a person can be sent to the row for killing a police dog, then some *person* who's supposed to be responsible for the dog needs to get dropped in there if the dog wastes an innocent person. I would assume that would be it's partner, but no idea really.<br>
