<br>
FYI.  Not all animals used in testing are destroyed during the testing process.  When I was in college my roomates had snakes.  Now snakes can get a little costly to feed, but they lucked out and got ahold of a bunch of rats that had been used in some kind of animal testing.  The rats were perfectly healthy, but they were useless to the researchers and were going to be destroyed.  My roommates got them, gave them to another friend who was studing herpitology, and they raised themselves some rats. <p>Level 55 rogue of The Tribunal, and member in good standing of Equilibrium. <br>
